  "text": "PageRank, as a link analysis algorithm, was first proposed [CITATION_1] to calculate webpage importance for query in World Wide Web, and used by Google search engine for years. The heuristic underlying PageRank is that importance of a page, also ranking, is proportional to its parents' importance, and inversely proportional to outgoing degree L(). In general, the PageRank value for any page Pj can be expressed as:",
